{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CcL3NaZdQ9GHQDm5Jjuj47","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     2→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     3→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     4→\n     5→  <parent>\n     6→    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n     7→    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>\n     8→    <version>3.3.7</version>\n     9→    <relativePath/>\n    10→  </parent>\n    11→\n    12→  <groupId>example</groupId>\n    13→  <artifactId>order-boot</artifactId>\n    14→  <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n    15→  <name>order-boot</name>\n    16→  <packaging>jar</packaging>\n    17→\n    18→  <properties>\n    19→    <java.version>17</java.version>\n    20→    <joinfaces.version>5.5.6</joinfaces.version>\n    21→    <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>\n    22→    <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>\n    23→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    24→  </properties>\n    25→\n    26→  <dependencyManagement>\n    27→    <dependencies>\n    28→      <dependency>\n    29→        <groupId>org.joinfaces</groupId>\n    30→        <artifactId>joinfaces-bom</artifactId>\n    31→        <version>${joinfaces.version}</version>\n    32→        <type>pom</type>\n    33→        <scope>import</scope>\n    34→      </dependency>\n    35→    </dependencies>\n    36→  </dependencyManagement>\n    37→\n    38→  <dependencies>\n    39→    <dependency>\n    40→      <groupId>org.joinfaces</groupId>\n    41→      <artifactId>primefaces-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>\n    42→    </dependency>\n    43→    <dependency>\n    44→      <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    45→      <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>\n    46→    </dependency>\n    47→    <dependency>\n    48→      <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    49→      <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    50→      <version>2.2.224</version>\n    51→      <scope>runtime</scope>\n    52→    </dependency>\n    53→    <dependency>\n    54→      <groupId>jakarta.inject</groupId>\n    55→      <artifactId>jakarta.inject-api</artifactId>\n    56→    </dependency>\n    57→  </dependencies>\n    58→\n    59→  <build>\n    60→    <plugins>\n    61→      <plugin>\n    62→        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    63→        <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    64→      </plugin>\n    65→    </plugins>\n    66→  </build>\n    67→</project>\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937f5c14-6c2e-425e-831b-fd6be18e2599","uuid":"f1df35fb-f68a-4cce-8d5e-4bac44e268db"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GQr2fEQG1izreEQnpDRiRx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"package\", \"spring-boot:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937f5c14-6c2e-425e-831b-fd6be18e2599","uuid":"df452a46-b50b-413b-bbf3-9a359d9fa7d8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GGFSr5R7Tp1xsyFoHDzGX2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.port=8081\n     2→\n     3→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb\n     4→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n     5→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     6→spring.datasource.password=\n     7→\n     8→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     9→spring.jpa.show-sql=true\n    10→spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\n    11→\n    12→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    13→spring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n    14→\n    15→joinfaces.faces.PROJECT_STAGE=Development\n    16→joinfaces.primefaces.theme=saga\n    17→\n    18→logging.level.com.example.orderspring=INFO\n    19→logging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=DEBUG\n    20→logging.level.org.hibernate.type.descriptor.sql=TRACE\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937f5c14-6c2e-425e-831b-fd6be18e2599","uuid":"1f31591a-9077-4e1c-afef-889e51610886"}
