{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01G5L9JCqdUikvz7g2oeTZ1h","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_018DLZQA5zXb7qjyFd3f1Lzh","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__order__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/example/orderspring/repository/LineItemRepository.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3666,"cache_read_input_tokens":129834,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3666,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":303},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937f5c14-6c2e-425e-831b-fd6be18e2599","uuid":"64bd37b1-0f14-4ca7-9907-5251243a553a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DejK3Ru2RRmyeDMesneZfU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.Part;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.entity.PartKey;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→import java.util.Optional;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class PartRepository {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    EntityManager em;\n    17→\n    18→    public List<Part> findAllParts() {\n    19→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT p FROM Part p ORDER BY p.partNumber\", Part.class)\n    20→                .getResultList();\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    public Optional<Part> findByPartNumberAndRevision(String partNumber, int revision) {\n    24→        PartKey key = new PartKey(partNumber, revision);\n    25→        Part part = em.find(Part.class, key);\n    26→        return Optional.ofNullable(part);\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public Part save(Part part) {\n    30→        PartKey key = new PartKey(part.getPartNumber(), part.getRevision());\n    31→        Part existing = em.find(Part.class, key);\n    32→        if (existing == null) {\n    33→            em.persist(part);\n    34→            return part;\n    35→        } else {\n    36→            return em.merge(part);\n    37→        }\n    38→    }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937f5c14-6c2e-425e-831b-fd6be18e2599","uuid":"b49b7afd-7bce-4c6f-b8c6-8cd255e7cdf9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DLZQA5zXb7qjyFd3f1Lzh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItem;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItemKey;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@ApplicationScoped\n    12→public class LineItemRepository {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    EntityManager em;\n    16→\n    17→    public List<LineItem> findAllLineItems() {\n    18→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT l FROM LineItem l\", LineItem.class)\n    19→                .getResultList();\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    public List<LineItem> findLineItemsByOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    23→        return em.createQuery(\n    24→                \"SELECT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId ORDER BY l.itemId\",\n    25→                LineItem.class)\n    26→                .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n    27→                .getResultList();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public LineItem findLineItemById(int itemId, Integer orderId) {\n    31→        List<LineItem> results = em.createQuery(\n    32→                \"SELECT DISTINCT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.itemId = :itemId AND l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\",\n    33→                LineItem.class)\n    34→                .setParameter(\"itemId\", itemId)\n    35→                .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n    36→                .getResultList();\n    37→        return results.isEmpty() ? null : results.get(0);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public LineItem save(LineItem lineItem) {\n    41→        if (em.contains(lineItem)) {\n    42→            return em.merge(lineItem);\n    43→        }\n    44→        // Check if entity already exists\n    45→        LineItemKey key = new LineItemKey(lineItem.getCustomerOrder().getOrderId(), lineItem.getItemId());\n    46→        LineItem existing = em.find(LineItem.class, key);\n    47→        if (existing == null) {\n    48→            em.persist(lineItem);\n    49→            return lineItem;\n    50→        } else {\n    51→            return em.merge(lineItem);\n    52→        }\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    public void deleteAllByOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    56→        em.createQuery(\"DELETE FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\")\n    57→                .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n    58→                .executeUpdate();\n    59→        em.flush();\n    60→    }\n    61→}\n    62→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937f5c14-6c2e-425e-831b-fd6be18e2599","uuid":"02fd2ff1-c7a5-46ac-b5b9-8b409f0e82b7"}
